description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about ensuring cancer care still takes place in a COVID-19 environment? Join the Royal Marsden, a dedicated specialist cancer hospital, where we have continued to deliver both diagnostics, research and treatment as a COVID-19 protected site. The Royal Marsden is the largest comprehensive cancer centre in Europe with an international reputation for high-quality patient care, research, development and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Ward Sister in the Cancer Services Division. We are seeking a permanent ward sister / charge nurse band 7 to manage Bud Flanagan East Ward. This is a 16 bed Haematology unit predominantly caring for patient’s pre and post stem cell transplant. Our unit commitment is to meet the Trust’s goals of excellence in caring for our patients, their families and friends with professionalism, respect and dignity. We are an inclusive team and would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a committed, enthusiastic and self-motivated experienced haematology nurse to join our well established and diverse team. As the ward manager you will be expected to act as a clinical leader and role model. The ideal candidate will have had experience as a ward manager and will need to demonstrate a pro-active and adaptive approach to leadership and management with a positive mind-set and hold an interest in working within a fast moving and busy ward. They must be a good and effective communicator, who can demonstrate problem solving skills with the ability to work under pressure, managing staff and delivering patient focused care. They will be able to demonstrate flexibility to meet the varied demands of the role as required. This highly rewarding role includes a mixture of clinical and managerial shifts Monday to Friday, including long days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are excellent development and educational opportunities available in addition to good staff benefits such as childcare voucher scheme, an onsite nursery and a highly regarded staff support service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aly Foyle, Matron, Alyson.foyle@rmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
